At Lockheed Martin, we believe that by applying the highest standards of business ethics and forward-thinking, everything is within our reach – and yours as a Lockheed Martin employee. We value your unique skills and expertise, and we aim to give back continuously by offering a wide variety of benefits and amenities to help our employees live flexible, balanced, and fulfilling lives at, and outside of, work. Lockheed Martin Rotary and Mission Systems has an opportunity for an early career AI/ML Engineer supporting the Electronic Warfare (EW) program area. As an early career hire on our Engineering team, you can help us take on the world’s most important and complex challenges by providing solutions to a variety of technical problems of moderate scope and complexity under general supervision. In this important role, you will collaborate with a diverse team of technical professionals and interact with outside customers. The successful candidate will be flexible, motivated, dedicated, detail-focused, team-oriented, and capable of multi-tasking. Position Responsibilities performed to complete milestones associated with specific projects:  Translate requirements and apply to developing, implementing, and deploying autonomy and artificial intelligence algorithms for LM products and platforms;  Implements algorithms to train systems to recognize patterns and perform specific functions;  Responsible for various phases of developing, testing, troubleshooting and maintaining autonomy software.  Develops human-machine interface scenarios, breaking missions into tasks; 


